🔹 9) Web Response Time Script
#!/bin/bash

URLS=("https://example.com" "https://google.com")

for URL in "${URLS[@]}"
do
    RESPONSE_TIME=$(curl -o /dev/null -s -w '%{time_total}' $URL)
    echo "Response time for $URL: $RESPONSE_TIME seconds"
done
✔ Explanation:
array stores URLs
curl -w '%{time_total}' → measures time
-s → silent mode
